Spectacular
Pragmatic       => dealing with things sensibly and realistically in a way that is based on practical rather than theoretical considerations
Tutelage        => instruction; tuition. "he felt privileged to be under the tutelage of an experienced actor"
Lucid           => expressed clearly; easy to understand.
Fidget          => make small movements, especially of the hands and feet, through nervousness or impatience; be impatient or uneasy.
Discretion      => the quality of behaving or speaking in such a way as to avoid causing offence or revealing confidential information.
Pry             => enquire too inquisitively into a person's private affairs.
Strangle        => to obstruct seriously or fatally the normal breathing of
Reconcile       => restore friendly behavior
Incumbent       => The incumbent is the current holder of a political office; necessary for (someone) as a duty or responsibility; obligatory
